modules.description: This module provides operations for creating, modifying, and querying ordered key-value maps, including adding, removing, merging, and iterating over bindings. It works with ordered maps and sequences, enabling tasks like filtering, folding, and converting between map and list representations. Use cases include processing structured data, managing configurations, or building dynamic mappings from sequential inputs.

Processes text by tokenizing, stemming, and removing stop words using string and list operations. Works with raw input strings and produces structured lists of processed tokens. Used to prepare textual data for analysis or machine learning pipelines.

manages ordered key-value mappings with operations for insertion, deletion, merging, and iteration, supporting transformations between maps and lists. It handles sequences and ordered structures, enabling filtering, folding, and dynamic data construction. Users can manipulate structured data, adjust configurations, or build mappings from input streams. Examples include merging multiple configuration maps or extracting specific entries from a large dataset.
